# Suppress AVD-DS-0002 (Image user should not be 'root') — NUT requires root at
# container init for two reasons:
# 1. upsdrvctl (driver startup) accesses /dev/bus/usb/* via libusb, which
#    requires root (or CAP_SYS_RAWIO + udev rules tuned for the host).
# 2. The entrypoint chowns /etc/nut + /var/run/nut to the nut user before
#    exec'ing upsd.
# upsd (the daemon serving port 3493) drops to user "nut" internally via the
# --with-user=nut --with-group=nut configure flags used at build time. So the
# long-running NUT process IS non-root — only the container init is.
AVD-DS-0002
